title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch 22 Starlink satellites on Falcon 9 rocket launch from Cape Canaveral
summary: The mission comes a little more than 12 hours after SpaceX performed a static fire test of the rocket Monday night. Liftoff of the Starlink 10-5 mission is set for 9:20 a.m. EDT (1320 UTC).

title: SpaceX completes static fire of Falcon 9 rocket ahead of Starlink and Crew 9 missions
summary: The booster will first launch the Starlink 10-5 mission no earlier than the morning of Tuesday, Aug. 20. The static fire test happened Monday evening shortly after 7 p.m. EDT (2300 UTC).
